1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,533
welcome back

2
00:00:01,533 --> 00:00:06,600
today we are going to work on the stuff we had left over in the past episodes

3
00:00:06,766 --> 00:00:09,833
since this stuff is also covered by quests

4
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:13,033
let's start by opening the next chapter of our book

5
00:00:13,266 --> 00:00:17,166
after being reminded that we are entering the work in progress area

6
00:00:17,166 --> 00:00:20,600
we find a quest that remind us of our hypogen needs

7
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:22,200
we quickly complete it

8
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:24,866
and then we get reminded on our main objective

9
00:00:24,866 --> 00:00:27,566
a hypogen coil plasma forge

10
00:00:27,866 --> 00:00:30,800
making 16 coils for the quest is easy

11
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:34,100
but we have no use for such low amount of coils

12
00:00:34,233 --> 00:00:36,766
we need 2000 for our DTPF

13
00:00:36,766 --> 00:00:39,433
or 900 for a blast furnace

14
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:43,033
and the next quest requires us to make space time

15
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:45,866
which is made in an hypogen plasma forge

16
00:00:45,866 --> 00:00:47,700
so this path is blocked

17
00:00:47,966 --> 00:00:49,233
on the other side

18
00:00:49,233 --> 00:00:53,766
after pulverizing one of the tesaracts we made to test our DTPF

19
00:00:53,766 --> 00:00:56,766
we obtained some transcendent metal dust

20
00:00:56,933 --> 00:00:59,766
cooking that stuff is incredibly expensive

21
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:02,566
the process also requires some tungsten

22
00:01:02,566 --> 00:01:05,633
that ends up becoming celestial in the process

23
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,766
and to cool it down

24
00:01:07,766 --> 00:01:11,500
we have to add super coolant and titan steel to the freezer

25
00:01:11,666 --> 00:01:14,400
while the reason is explained by the quest book

26
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:17,433
what we care about is that we now have the spiny ingot

27
00:01:17,866 --> 00:01:22,666
and that was one of the two materials we needed for our space elevator upgrade

28
00:01:22,766 --> 00:01:25,833
the other one is dimensionally shifted superfluid

29
00:01:25,966 --> 00:01:27,900
this requires a bunch of things

30
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:32,300
but the first ingredient we notice is the next grade of purified water

31
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:38,100
and before we can even start looking at how that new purification unit works

32
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:40,100
we notice a lack of quarks

33
00:01:40,266 --> 00:01:42,366
those are made in a cyclotron

34
00:01:42,366 --> 00:01:47,066
so let's repurpose our quantum anomaly set up to a quark isolator one

35
00:01:47,366 --> 00:01:49,633
once we obtained enough quarks

36
00:01:49,633 --> 00:01:52,066
we notice one slightly bigger issue

37
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:55,266
to craft the purification plant structure

38
00:01:55,266 --> 00:01:57,600
we need quite some diamonds

39
00:01:57,766 --> 00:02:02,833
which are mostly going into making 100,000 infinity ingots

40
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:04,666
since we have a DTPF

41
00:02:04,866 --> 00:02:08,100
it is probably a better option to use that instead

42
00:02:08,566 --> 00:02:09,000
however

43
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,666
while that recipe make a lot of infinity

44
00:02:11,666 --> 00:02:14,900
it is also eating a lot of resplendent catalyst

45
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,666
and that was with a 50 fuel discount

46
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:20,633
thanks to having fully breached the dimensional boundaries

47
00:02:20,633 --> 00:02:24,400
by making hypogen and neutronium for 8 hours straight

48
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:32,066
which means that our current DTPF fuel production plant running on 350 amps UHV is not enough

49
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:33,766
so we push it even further

50
00:02:33,766 --> 00:02:35,900
by doubling the amount of machines

51
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:39,000
while also wall sharing the expensive laser

52
00:02:39,266 --> 00:02:43,200
but the first thing we will want to do with our new Infinity source is

53
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,966
upgrade our component assembly line

54
00:02:45,966 --> 00:02:46,600
that way

55
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:48,466
we will be able to use less Infinity

56
00:02:48,466 --> 00:02:52,233
for the components required for our upcoming machines

57
00:02:52,466 --> 00:02:57,433
such as the blocks we needed for the last tier of water purification plant

58
00:02:57,500 --> 00:03:00,100
those expensive components are also needed

59
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:02,666
in the catalyst that this plant works with

60
00:03:02,666 --> 00:03:06,566
so after a day of intensively staring at our infinity stonks

61
00:03:06,566 --> 00:03:11,300
we managed to stock up enough materials to craft the required parts

62
00:03:11,666 --> 00:03:16,166
and after also getting the specialized quark catalysts

63
00:03:16,166 --> 00:03:19,900
we are ready to purify our water at subatomic levels

64
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:20,566
as usual

65
00:03:20,566 --> 00:03:23,233
we have to solve some logistical puzzle

66
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:25,266
to make that machine work

67
00:03:25,266 --> 00:03:26,800
after some tests

68
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,766
we figured out that

69
00:03:27,766 --> 00:03:31,366
this machine only cares about the sequence of inserted stuff

70
00:03:31,366 --> 00:03:33,100
so we did some math analysis

71
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:35,866
to find an optimal sequence of stuff to insert

72
00:03:35,866 --> 00:03:39,266
to find the correct combination as fast as possible

73
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:39,966
with that

74
00:03:39,966 --> 00:03:43,166
it was just a matter of doing a little bit of Redstone circuitry

75
00:03:43,166 --> 00:03:46,466
to properly manage the sequence loading and insertion

76
00:03:46,866 --> 00:03:51,200
and here you can see the train of quark releasing catalysts being loaded up

77
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,366
and then inserted in a fixed order

78
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:54,966
and with that

79
00:03:54,966 --> 00:03:58,200
we managed to obtain the subatomically perfected water

80
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,666
and the baryonic stabilized matter

81
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:04,000
which we merge into the dimensionally shifted superfluid

82
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,966
required for our new space elevator motors

83
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:07,733
with those

84
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:10,566
we can now run the Mining Modules MK3

85
00:04:10,566 --> 00:04:15,100
capable of sending drones far enough to collect draconic cores

86
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:18,300
but for the moment we only found trash

87
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,100
so you know the drill

88
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,700
while the new drills are being forged

89
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,800
we can do some new quests

90
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:27,833
and since we still haven't done the new components

91
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:30,033
let's see how those are made

92
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:35,466
the new weird material we have to use to handle the strength of 33 millions volts is

93
00:04:35,466 --> 00:04:37,466
proto-halkonite steel

94
00:04:37,666 --> 00:04:39,066
to get that material

95
00:04:39,066 --> 00:04:44,766
we start by coating an Infinity fine wire with a special blend of expensive materials

96
00:04:44,766 --> 00:04:46,833
once the first coating is done

97
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:51,900
we complete the material by freezing some dimensionally shifted superfluid around it

98
00:04:52,033 --> 00:04:56,233
after using this new material for all of the UIV components

99
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:58,000
we move on to the next the quest

100
00:04:58,100 --> 00:04:59,766
new superconductor

101
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:01,866
and here we face a new issue

102
00:05:01,866 --> 00:05:03,200
to work that stuff

103
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:07,266
we need an internal coil EBF or a hypogen coil DTPF

104
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:09,400
so you know the drill

105
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,400
we go do something else

106
00:05:11,566 --> 00:05:12,366
luckily

107
00:05:12,366 --> 00:05:18,666
it looks like our mining drones managed to find one draconic core schematic between all of the space trash

108
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,900
now we can craft draconic cores

109
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:23,866
and thus unlock the tier 2 fusion crafter

110
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,666
by the way

111
00:05:24,666 --> 00:05:26,633
to get the required ichorium

112
00:05:26,633 --> 00:05:31,000
we can now send a mining drone on some far asteroids to collect some

113
00:05:31,066 --> 00:05:32,833
and then we quickly infuse it

114
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:35,166
thus upgrading our Fusion Crafter

115
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:38,300
which we then upgrade again with the Wyvern stuff

116
00:05:38,366 --> 00:05:39,666
and with that

117
00:05:39,666 --> 00:05:43,000
we can finally craft Dragon blood out of cheap stuff

118
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:45,700
the reason we did that was to get more hypogen

119
00:05:45,766 --> 00:05:46,566
however

120
00:05:46,566 --> 00:05:48,566
getting there took us quite some time

121
00:05:48,566 --> 00:05:50,033
and in the meanwhile

122
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:53,466
our DTPF kept making hypogen to keep warm

123
00:05:53,466 --> 00:05:56,800
making already enough of for the new coils we needed

124
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,400
and I got to say

125
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,866
solidifying that material is a really hard task

126
00:06:02,066 --> 00:06:04,800
and after hours of solidifying screws

127
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,466
we managed to complete our new DTPF

128
00:06:08,066 --> 00:06:09,366
as with the old one

129
00:06:09,366 --> 00:06:10,700
to keep it warmed up

130
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:14,833
we set it up to make hypogen whenever there are no craftings queued up

131
00:06:15,366 --> 00:06:17,433
and this one with hypogen coils

132
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:20,266
can do the recipe that has twice the yield

133
00:06:20,566 --> 00:06:23,100
and it can also do new materials

134
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:24,566
such as space time

135
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:25,500
with that

136
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:28,366
we can finally craft crafting input buffers

137
00:06:28,366 --> 00:06:32,200
which will allow us to make better looking crafting setups

138
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:35,966
this input will indeed contain both solids and fluids

139
00:06:35,966 --> 00:06:37,000
have infinite caching

140
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:40,400
and separate the materials of the various recipes

141
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:46,033
but running 2 DTPF is starting to put too much of a strain on our generators

142
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:47,766
to boost our production

143
00:06:47,766 --> 00:06:50,666
we are going to throw some hypogen in our fuel

144
00:06:50,866 --> 00:06:56,433
and then we also add some of the leftover heavy radox from the radox polymer setup

145
00:06:56,633 --> 00:07:00,200
and now it is time to see how our new fuel does

146
00:07:00,366 --> 00:07:03,400
and it looks like it can fill up our battery in 3 weeks

147
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,666
with that extra production

148
00:07:05,666 --> 00:07:09,366
we can even do a bit of overclocking on our DTPFs

149
00:07:09,566 --> 00:07:10,466
to do so

150
00:07:10,466 --> 00:07:15,766
we can use a screwdriver to remove the throttle we previously applied to the power plug

151
00:07:16,466 --> 00:07:18,266
going back to our progression

152
00:07:18,266 --> 00:07:23,000
we can now use our new DTPF for making the new UIV superconductor

153
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,900
which we use for the new energy hatches

154
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:29,366
next we could work on the final tier of coils

155
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:32,066
however those look quite expensive

156
00:07:32,066 --> 00:07:32,833
not to mention

157
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:35,900
we won't get them with our current space time production

158
00:07:36,066 --> 00:07:37,633
looking for a solution

159
00:07:37,633 --> 00:07:40,300
we can try moving to the other quest branch

160
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:42,400
making a UMV circuit

161
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:46,666
which basically means just adding a new layer to our circuit factory

162
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:51,166
and behind that circuits hides a solution to our problems

163
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:54,633
with more power we can get spacetime faster

164
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:58,166
and the way we have to resort to get enough power at that stage

165
00:07:58,166 --> 00:08:01,266
is by harvesting all of the energy emitted by a whole star

166
00:08:01,266 --> 00:08:03,833
by building a Dyson sphere around it

167
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:08,000
and while the expensive parts of the structure are being crafted

168
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:14,200
we can work on the long chain of recursive crafts for modules we will be constantly launching in space

169
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,700
and here the main issue is two materials

170
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:18,633
which are not easy to come by

171
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:19,900
to get those

172
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:21,666
we can kidnap a couple of mobs

173
00:08:21,666 --> 00:08:24,333
and get some armors out of their clones

174
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:24,833
however

175
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:26,766
some of the dropped armors are damaged

176
00:08:26,766 --> 00:08:31,400
and our macerater doesn't like to recycle stuff that is not brand new

177
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:34,200
so to make it accept those items

178
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:37,600
we first have to repair them using an energetic infuser

179
00:08:37,766 --> 00:08:39,900
once we have tidied the wardrobe

180
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:43,233
we can send it through an industrial maceration stack

181
00:08:43,366 --> 00:08:44,366
and with that

182
00:08:44,366 --> 00:08:46,633
we can now start stocking up modules

183
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:48,666
for our upcoming Dyson Sphere

184
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:49,633
meanwhile

185
00:08:49,633 --> 00:08:53,033
the structure to launch those is not crafting properly

186
00:08:53,233 --> 00:08:55,266
the teseracts are not crafting

187
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:57,500
and our DTPF is not working

188
00:08:57,666 --> 00:09:00,500
the issue seems to be that we run out of fuel

189
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:04,466
our fuel plant indeed can't process fuel fast enough

190
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:09,466
the recipe has a base crafting time of almost 1 hour at UHV voltage

191
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:12,366
not once, but on multiple steps

192
00:09:12,366 --> 00:09:13,800
to fix that issue

193
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:16,033
we can now afford a plasma mixer

194
00:09:16,166 --> 00:09:20,900
that thing will do all of the steps in 5 seconds and with parallelization

195
00:09:21,066 --> 00:09:24,433
but there are no discounts on the amount of power used

196
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,400
indeed this machine is so power intensive

197
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,900
that no cable or laser can power it

198
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:32,033
how do we make it run then

199
00:09:32,233 --> 00:09:32,500
well

200
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:35,766
we can give it energy from the wireless network

201
00:09:36,066 --> 00:09:37,566
which is a virtual battery

202
00:09:37,566 --> 00:09:39,766
with virtually infinite power capacity

203
00:09:39,766 --> 00:09:43,900
that high tier laptonic capacitor banks can swap energy with

204
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:47,433
once the energy is rebalanced with the wireless battery

205
00:09:47,433 --> 00:09:49,100
we can use our mixer

206
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,566
but that didn't really fix the issue

207
00:09:51,566 --> 00:09:54,500
we just move it to our fusion reactors

208
00:09:54,666 --> 00:09:57,400
they can't keep up with all of those plasmas

209
00:09:57,800 --> 00:10:00,400
and that is not the only fusion issue

210
00:10:00,566 --> 00:10:04,166
we are also having trouble with the metastable oganesson production

211
00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:07,400
which is made by our smaller Mark 4 reactors

212
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,266
to fix those problems

213
00:10:09,266 --> 00:10:11,833
we should do a Mark 4 compact reactor

214
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,400
which will do higher parallels and

215
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,233
unlike its predecessors

216
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:17,966
has perfect overclocking

217
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:23,700
meaning it will be more than 16 times faster than the compact 3 on tier 1 plasmas

218
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:24,966
to craft it

219
00:10:24,966 --> 00:10:28,033
we only lack of platinum and one of the plastics

220
00:10:28,066 --> 00:10:30,500
usually to fix those issues

221
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,766
we would upgrade our stocking storage

222
00:10:32,766 --> 00:10:35,266
or find the bottleneck in our processing chain

223
00:10:35,266 --> 00:10:36,466
and speed it up

224
00:10:36,766 --> 00:10:37,166
however

225
00:10:37,166 --> 00:10:40,033
that is a task which has become hard to manage

226
00:10:40,033 --> 00:10:41,966
and is starting to cause lag

227
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:44,366
and we now have a better solution

228
00:10:44,366 --> 00:10:47,166
for those early game long processing chains

229
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:48,900
the quantum force transformer

230
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:51,666
can do the whole platline as a single recipient

231
00:10:51,666 --> 00:10:54,766
can be easily overclocked and parallelized

232
00:10:54,833 --> 00:10:58,633
and we won't have to work with any of the involved fluids

233
00:10:58,633 --> 00:10:59,633
for the plastic

234
00:10:59,633 --> 00:11:02,800
it won't simply do polybenzimidazole at once

235
00:11:02,966 --> 00:11:06,900
it will also do all of the other simpler polymers at the same time

236
00:11:06,966 --> 00:11:08,966
and here we have our new machine

237
00:11:08,966 --> 00:11:11,833
making a lot of plastics in a single step

238
00:11:11,966 --> 00:11:14,100
while our plastics are stocking up

239
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:17,400
we can make a second machine for processing platinum

240
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:19,866
and since this machine is super fast

241
00:11:19,866 --> 00:11:22,566
even with low amount of catalyst and power

242
00:11:22,566 --> 00:11:24,766
we can clean up the old platline

243
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:25,966
meanwhile

244
00:11:25,966 --> 00:11:30,800
we have managed to gather all the ingredients required for our new fusion reactor

245
00:11:30,966 --> 00:11:34,833
and after building some more machines to process everything

246
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:37,200
we managed to complete our new reactor

247
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,000
this reactor is so fast

248
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,866
that the bottleneck is now our plasma mixer

249
00:11:42,066 --> 00:11:43,866
but we can quickly fix that issue

250
00:11:43,866 --> 00:11:46,066
by increasing its maximum parallel

251
00:11:46,066 --> 00:11:48,200
and letting it eat our whole battery

252
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,866
while the mixer waits for the leftover energy

253
00:11:50,866 --> 00:11:53,033
to be sent into the wireless network

254
00:11:53,033 --> 00:11:55,033
we can work on building more machines

255
00:11:55,033 --> 00:11:58,033
to speed up the crafting speed of our Dyson Sphere

256
00:11:58,366 --> 00:12:00,833
and we can even build machines in parallel

257
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:04,066
by using Loki Ring from the Funny Flower mod

258
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:06,666
and with all of those new machines

259
00:12:06,666 --> 00:12:10,266
we quickly complete all of the parts of our new source of power

260
00:12:10,266 --> 00:12:11,633
the Dyson Sphere

261
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,200
the issue of that structure

262
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,700
is that the modules we use to encase a star

263
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,966
can end up gliding and thus break

264
00:12:18,066 --> 00:12:20,566
so we have to constantly feed new modules

265
00:12:20,566 --> 00:12:24,666
and some computation to better calculate the module trajectories

266
00:12:24,666 --> 00:12:27,000
lowering the needed replacements

267
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:30,266
to move all of that energy back to our base

268
00:12:30,266 --> 00:12:33,000
we could craft one more really ultimate battery

269
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:36,166
but I think a wormhole generator sounds cooler

270
00:12:36,433 --> 00:12:38,400
with that we now have enough power

271
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:41,000
to further speed up our hypogen production

272
00:12:41,266 --> 00:12:44,166
with the power of 40,000 UHV amps

273
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:48,066
our production went from half ingot to more than 2 every second

274
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:51,233
to further increase our plasma forging capacity

275
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:54,766
we use the hypogen to multiply our DTPFs

276
00:12:55,033 --> 00:12:58,566
and even with 4 DTPFs running at that power

277
00:12:58,566 --> 00:13:02,500
we are still making less than one ingot of space time each second

278
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:05,700
however if we manage to get eternal coils

279
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:11,400
we can use a recipe that will use less than half the ingredients to make four times as much

280
00:13:11,566 --> 00:13:14,033
the main issue is that eternal coils

281
00:13:14,033 --> 00:13:16,433
other than requiring quite some space time

282
00:13:16,433 --> 00:13:17,966
and a UIV circuit

283
00:13:17,966 --> 00:13:20,766
also require an eternal singularity

284
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:22,600
getting these is quite expensive

285
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:24,500
and also needs some stuff

286
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:27,700
such as Soul Sand which we haven't really automated

287
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:31,466
when we needed a couple of blocks for a single singularity

288
00:13:31,466 --> 00:13:32,466
it was doable

289
00:13:32,466 --> 00:13:34,800
now we have to find a better way

290
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:38,666
and I think the best way is to not use soul sand at all

291
00:13:38,666 --> 00:13:43,200
we can get a singularity by compressing a little bit of space time

292
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:43,700
however

293
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:46,300
that requires a stabilized black hole

294
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:49,166
which is a whole new rabbit hole to explore

295
00:13:49,366 --> 00:13:51,466
and I think that is a good moment to

296
00:13:51,466 --> 00:13:52,600
start working on that

297
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:55,666
since this is the last main quest of the current tier

298
00:13:55,866 --> 00:13:59,033
so after working millions of iron dusts

299
00:13:59,033 --> 00:14:00,600
we managed to build a structure

300
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,600
strong enough to support and contain a black hole

301
00:14:03,766 --> 00:14:06,833
this machine has some peculiar requirements

302
00:14:06,966 --> 00:14:07,266
first

303
00:14:07,266 --> 00:14:10,200
we need a black hole seed to open a black hole

304
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,033
so we can compress stuff

305
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:15,066
once the black hole becomes too unstable

306
00:14:15,066 --> 00:14:16,800
we close it with a collapsar

307
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:19,766
so once everything is ready

308
00:14:19,766 --> 00:14:22,166
we can throw a black hole seed into the machine

309
00:14:22,166 --> 00:14:23,833
and admire our creation

310
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:27,566
which we use to craft eternal singularities

311
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:31,400
however our black hole is going to slowly decay

312
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:33,966
thus becoming unusable for the task

313
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,500
and in that state

314
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:38,433
it is going to void our ingredients

315
00:14:38,466 --> 00:14:41,466
so we make it collapse to clean up the machine

316
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:45,000
and now it is time to fully automate that process

317
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:47,200
after doing a little bit of math

318
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,400
we find out that

319
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:51,200
by also adding some extra stabilizer

320
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:56,500
we can craft a batch of 2800 singularities with a single black hole

321
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:59,600
so we quickly build a custom AE2 pattern

322
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:02,300
with all of the stuff that we will have to use

323
00:15:02,666 --> 00:15:04,000
the items will be split

324
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:07,600
so that a group of timers can properly manage the black hole

325
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:12,266
the first one is going to let the black hole get close to the end of its lifespan

326
00:15:12,466 --> 00:15:13,900
during this phase

327
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:18,233
the black hole will allow us to do 88 singularities at a time

328
00:15:18,566 --> 00:15:19,200
then

329
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,000
just before the critical point

330
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,233
the timer will trigger a second timer

331
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:28,400
which will halt the decay of our black hole by inserting liquid space time inside it

332
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:31,400
the material costs grows exponentially

333
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:31,633
so

334
00:15:31,633 --> 00:15:35,033
we do not want to let this process go on for too much time

335
00:15:35,033 --> 00:15:36,633
and at this stage

336
00:15:36,633 --> 00:15:41,866
our black hole will compress 350 items at once

337
00:15:42,666 --> 00:15:46,033
and once the stabilizer cost becomes too high

338
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:47,600
we collapse the hole

339
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:50,633
now that we have enough singularities

340
00:15:50,633 --> 00:15:54,200
we can start working on the last tier of heating coils

341
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:57,500
and that required us to build a new set of solidifiers

342
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,966
to get all of the ingots and screws

343
00:16:00,266 --> 00:16:03,600
then our array of wire factories prepared the cabling

344
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:08,100
finally with all of our 14 generic purpose assembly lines

345
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:10,633
we slowly crafted the new coils

346
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:15,666
while we craft the 7000 coils required for the DTPF upgrade

347
00:16:15,666 --> 00:16:20,166
we can also use the singularities for upgrading our ore facility

348
00:16:20,433 --> 00:16:23,300
the issue is that we can't let our ore facility run

349
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:26,266
because it will quickly clog our storage room

350
00:16:26,466 --> 00:16:29,200
but now we can afford better storage

351
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:35,433
and we are going to use it to stock up the stuff we are making in unlimited amount right on the production site

352
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:36,433
meanwhile

353
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:38,766
after fixing the AFK counter

354
00:16:38,766 --> 00:16:42,700
we stocked up enough coils to upgrade our DTPFs

355
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:43,500
with those

356
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:45,866
we can now make cheaper space time

357
00:16:45,866 --> 00:16:47,200
cheaper hypogen

358
00:16:47,266 --> 00:16:49,966
one stack of Infinity out of a single catalyst

359
00:16:49,966 --> 00:16:52,166
and many other latter game recipes

360
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:53,200
and with that

361
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:55,900
I think we can close this chapter

362
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:59,000
so what was the lesson of today's episode

363
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,833
always build your fusion reactors in a tunnel

364
00:17:01,833 --> 00:17:03,266
for nice visuals

365
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:06,666
see you next time for even bigger multi blocks

366
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:07,666
bye bye

367
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,533
欢迎回来！

368
00:00:01,533 --> 00:00:06,600
今天要做的是前几集遗漏的东西

369
00:00:06,766 --> 00:00:09,833
而它们也在任务中有提及

370
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:13,033
让我们从这本书的下一章开始

371
00:00:13,266 --> 00:00:17,166
在被提醒我们进入半成品区后

372
00:00:17,166 --> 00:00:20,600
这里有个任务需要海珀珍

373
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:22,200
我们快速完成它

374
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:24,866
然后我们想起了主要目标

375
00:00:24,866 --> 00:00:27,566
海珀珍等离子锻炉

376
00:00:27,866 --> 00:00:30,800

制作16个线圈完成任务很简单


377
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:34,100
但是这个量少得没用

378
00:00:34,233 --> 00:00:36,766
我们的DTPF需要2112个

379
00:00:36,766 --> 00:00:39,433
巨型高炉需要864个

380
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:43,033
下一个任务要求我们创造时空

381
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:45,866
它是在海珀珍DTPF中制造的

382
00:00:45,866 --> 00:00:47,700
所以这条路行不通

383
00:00:47,966 --> 00:00:49,233

另一方面


384
00:00:49,233 --> 00:00:53,766
在粉碎了用来测试DTPF而制作的粗制超立方体后

385
00:00:53,766 --> 00:00:56,766
我们得到了超时空金属粉

386
00:00:56,933 --> 00:00:59,766
烧制那东西非常贵

387
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:02,566
这个过程还需要一些钨

388
00:01:02,566 --> 00:01:05,633
在这个过程中最终变成了天体钨等离子体

389
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,766
而想让它冷却下来

390
00:01:07,766 --> 00:01:11,500
我们得往冰箱里加超级冷却剂和泰坦精钢

391
00:01:11,666 --> 00:01:14,400
虽然任务书解释了原因

392
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:17,433
我们关心的是有转转锭了

393
00:01:17,866 --> 00:01:22,666
那是我们升级太空电梯所需的两种材料之一

394
00:01:22,766 --> 00:01:25,833
另一个是纬度偏移超流体

395
00:01:25,966 --> 00:01:27,900
这需要一堆材料

396
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:32,300
但是我们注意到的第一种成分是级八水

397
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:38,100
在我们开始研究新的净化装置如何工作之前

398
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:40,100
我们发现缺少夸克

399
00:01:40,266 --> 00:01:42,366
这些都是用回旋加速器制造的

400
00:01:42,366 --> 00:01:47,066
所以让我们把量子异常设备改成夸克分离器

401
00:01:47,366 --> 00:01:49,633
一旦得到足够的夸克

402
00:01:49,633 --> 00:01:52,066

我们又发现更严重一点的问题


403
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:55,266
要制作净化工厂的结构方块

404
00:01:55,266 --> 00:01:57,600
我们需要相当多的钻石

405
00:01:57,766 --> 00:02:02,833
主要用于制造十万个无限锭

406
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:04,666
既然我们有DTPF

407
00:02:04,866 --> 00:02:08,100
使用它可能是一个更好的选择

408
00:02:08,566 --> 00:02:09,000
然而

409
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,666
虽然这个配方产出大量的无尽

410
00:02:11,666 --> 00:02:14,900
它也在吞噬大量的光辉催化剂

411
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,666
这甚至是在有50%的燃料折扣下发生的

412
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:21,900
这折扣是通过连续8小时制造海珀珍和中子

413
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:24,366
成功突破维度界限带来的

414
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:32,066
这意味着350A UHV耗能的燃料生产是远远不够的

415
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:33,766
所以我们更进一步

416
00:02:33,766 --> 00:02:35,900
通过将机器数量增加一倍

417
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:39,000
同时共用昂贵的激光仓

418
00:02:39,266 --> 00:02:43,200

不过有了更快更好的无限来源后的第一件事


419
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,966
是升级部件装配线

420
00:02:45,966 --> 00:02:46,600
这样子

421
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:48,466
我们能用更少的无限锭

422
00:02:48,466 --> 00:02:52,233
来生产即将到来的机器所需的组件

423
00:02:52,466 --> 00:02:57,433
比如最后一级净水厂所需的方块

424
00:02:57,500 --> 00:03:00,100
这净水厂的催化剂

425
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:02,666
也这需要价值高昂的材料

426
00:03:02,666 --> 00:03:06,566
在密切关注无尽的库存后

427
00:03:06,566 --> 00:03:11,300
我们储备了足够制作所需的部件的材料

428
00:03:11,666 --> 00:03:16,166

在得到了特定的夸克催化剂后


429
00:03:16,166 --> 00:03:19,900

我们已经准备好在亚原子层面上净化我们的水


430
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:20,566
像往常一样

431
00:03:20,566 --> 00:03:23,233

我们必须解决一些物流问题


432
00:03:23,233 --> 00:03:25,266
来让那台机器工作

433
00:03:25,266 --> 00:03:26,800
经过一些测试

434
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,766
我们发现

435
00:03:27,766 --> 00:03:31,366
这台机器只关心物品输入的序列

436
00:03:31,366 --> 00:03:33,100
所以我们做了一些数学分析

437
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:35,866
找到一个最佳的输入序列

438
00:03:35,866 --> 00:03:39,266
用来尽快找到正确的组合

439
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:39,966
有了那个

440
00:03:39,966 --> 00:03:43,166

这不过是搭一些红石线缆


441
00:03:43,166 --> 00:03:46,466

来管理序列正确加载和插入的问题


442
00:03:46,866 --> 00:03:51,200
你可以看到一列夸克释放催化剂被装载起来

443
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,366
然后按固定顺序插入

444
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:54,966
有了这个

445
00:03:54,966 --> 00:03:58,200
我们就得到了理想微粒水（八级水）

446
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,666
以及重子稳定物质

447
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:04,000
我们将其合并成维度偏移超流体

448
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,966
用来制作新的太空电梯加速轨道

449
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:07,733
用那些

450
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:10,566
我们现在可以运行采矿模块MK3

451
00:04:10,566 --> 00:04:15,100
将无人机送到足够远的地方收集龙芯

452
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:18,300
但目前我们只找到垃圾

453
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,100

现在你知道下一步怎么“钻”了


454
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,700
当新钻头被锻造时

455
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,800
我们可以做一些新的任务

456
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:27,833
由于我们还没有完成新的组件

457
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:30,033
让我们看看这些是如何制作的

458
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:35,466

这种能够承载3300万伏的神必新材料是


459
00:04:35,466 --> 00:04:37,466
原初恒坚钢

460
00:04:37,666 --> 00:04:39,066
想获得它的话

461
00:04:39,066 --> 00:04:44,766
我们首先用一种昂贵的材料涂抹细无尽导线

462
00:04:44,766 --> 00:04:46,833
一旦涂层完成

463
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:51,900
我们通过在附近冻结超维度偏移超流体来完成材料

464
00:04:52,033 --> 00:04:56,233
在将这种新材料用于所有UIV组件后

465
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:58,000
我们继续下一个任务

466
00:04:58,100 --> 00:04:59,766
新的超导体

467
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:01,866
现在我们面临一个新问题

468
00:05:01,866 --> 00:05:03,200
去生产那东西

469
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:07,266
我们需要一个永恒高炉或者海珀珍DTPF

470
00:05:07,633 --> 00:05:09,400

接下来怎么办就很明白了


471
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,400
我们去做点别的

472
00:05:11,566 --> 00:05:12,366
幸运地

473
00:05:12,366 --> 00:05:16,466
看来我们的采矿无人机在所有太空垃圾之间

474
00:05:16,466 --> 00:05:18,666
找到了一个龙芯示意图

475
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,900
现在我们可以制作龙芯了

476
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:23,866
从而解锁二级聚合机械方块

477
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,666
顺便说一下

478
00:05:24,666 --> 00:05:26,633
为了获得所需的灵宝

479
00:05:26,633 --> 00:05:31,000
我们可以通过太空钻机来挖一点

480
00:05:31,066 --> 00:05:32,833
然后我们快速注魔

481
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:35,166
从而升级我们的龙研聚合

482
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:38,300
然后我们用双足飞龙再次升级

483
00:05:38,366 --> 00:05:39,666
有了这个

484
00:05:39,666 --> 00:05:43,000
我们终于可以用便宜的东西制作龙血了

485
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:45,700
我们这样做的原因是获得更多的海珀珍

486
00:05:45,766 --> 00:05:46,566
然而

487
00:05:46,566 --> 00:05:48,566
做出那些东西花了我们不少时间

488
00:05:48,566 --> 00:05:50,033
与此同时

489
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:53,466
我们的DTPF一直在制造海珀珍来保持维度超越

490
00:05:53,466 --> 00:05:56,800
新线圈材料已经足够

491
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,400
我不得不说

492
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,866
固化这种材料是一项非常艰巨的任务

493
00:06:02,066 --> 00:06:04,800

经过数小时的固化螺丝


494
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,466
我们设法完成了新的DTPF

495
00:06:08,066 --> 00:06:09,366
和旧的一样

496
00:06:09,366 --> 00:06:10,700
让它保持运作

497
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:12,766
只要没有主动下单

498
00:06:12,766 --> 00:06:14,833
就让它制作海珀珍

499
00:06:15,366 --> 00:06:17,433
有了海珀珍线圈

500
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:20,266
可以用两倍产量的配方了

501
00:06:20,566 --> 00:06:23,100
它还可以制造新材料

502
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:24,566
比如时空

503
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:25,500
有了那个

504
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:28,366
我们终于可以制作样板输入总成了

505
00:06:28,366 --> 00:06:32,200
这让我们做出更好看的自动化方案

506
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:35,966
这个输入包含固体和液体

507
00:06:35,966 --> 00:06:37,000
有无限缓存

508
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:40,400
并将各种配方的材料分开

509
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:46,033
但运行2个DTPF给发电机上太多压力了

510
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:47,766
为了提高发电量

511
00:06:47,766 --> 00:06:50,666
我们要往燃料里加点海珀珍

512
00:06:50,866 --> 00:06:53,433
我们还往燃料里勾兑了一些

513
00:06:53,433 --> 00:06:56,433
从拉多聚合物中提取的重拉多X

514
00:06:56,633 --> 00:07:00,200
现在是时候看看新燃料的能耐

515
00:07:00,366 --> 00:07:03,400
看起来它可以在3周内充满我们的电池

516
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,666
有了这额外的发电

517
00:07:05,666 --> 00:07:09,366
我们甚至可以在DTPF上做一点超频

518
00:07:09,566 --> 00:07:10,466
为此

519
00:07:10,466 --> 00:07:15,766
我们可以用螺丝刀移除之前在激光仓设置的上限

520
00:07:16,466 --> 00:07:18,266
回到主线

521
00:07:18,266 --> 00:07:23,000
我们现在可以使用新DTPF来制造新的UIV超导

522
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,900
将其用于新能源仓

523
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:29,366
接下来做最后一级线圈

524
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:32,066
然而，这些看起来很贵

525
00:07:32,066 --> 00:07:32,833
更不用说

526
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:35,900
以我们现在的时空产量是远远不够的

527
00:07:36,066 --> 00:07:37,633
寻找解决方案

528
00:07:37,633 --> 00:07:40,300
我们可以尝试转移到另一个任务分支

529
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:42,400
制作UMV电路

530
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:46,666
这基本上意味着在我们的电路工厂中新添加一层

531
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:51,166
在电路的背后隐藏着解决问题的方法

532
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:52,566
有了更多的能量

533
00:07:52,566 --> 00:07:54,633
我们可以更快地制造时空

534
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:58,166
在此阶段获得能量的最佳方法

535
00:07:58,166 --> 00:08:01,266
是收集整个恒星发出的所有能量

536
00:08:01,266 --> 00:08:03,833
通过在它周围建造一个戴森球

537
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:08,000
在昂贵的结构方块制作的同时

538
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:14,200
我们给将不断送入太空的模块的套娃合成自动化

539
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,700
主要问题是两种材料

540
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:18,633
这并不容易获得

541
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:19,900

为了获得它们


542
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:21,666
我们可以绑架几个怪

543
00:08:21,666 --> 00:08:24,333
从他们的克隆体中得到一些盔甲

544
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:24,833
然而

545
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:26,766
一些掉落的盔甲损坏了

546
00:08:26,766 --> 00:08:31,400
我们的粉碎机不喜欢回收旧物品

547
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:34,200
所以为了让它接受这些物品

548
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:37,600
我们首先得用能量注入器修复它们

549
00:08:37,766 --> 00:08:39,900
一旦我们整理好衣柜

550
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:43,233
我们把它送入工业粉碎机

551
00:08:43,366 --> 00:08:44,366
有了这个

552
00:08:44,366 --> 00:08:46,633
对于即将到来的戴森球

553
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:48,666
我们可以开始储备模块了

554
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:49,633
同时

555
00:08:49,633 --> 00:08:53,033
戴森球的结构方块并没有被正确制造

556
00:08:53,233 --> 00:08:55,266
粗制超立方体并没有在制作

557
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:57,500
而且我们的DTPF也停止工作了

558
00:08:57,666 --> 00:09:00,500
问题似乎是燃料用完了

559
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:04,466
我们的燃料工厂确实不够快

560
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:09,466
该配方在UHV下的基础制作时间大概是1小时

561
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:12,366

不止一步，好几步都这样


562
00:09:12,366 --> 00:09:13,800

为了解决这个问题


563
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:16,033
我们可以推出等离子搅拌机了

564
00:09:16,166 --> 00:09:20,900
它可以并行地在五秒内完成所有配方

565
00:09:21,066 --> 00:09:24,433
但耗电量没有折扣

566
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,400
确实，这台机器是如此耗电

567
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,900
没有电缆或激光可以为它供电

568
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:32,033
那么我们如何让它运行呢？

569
00:09:32,233 --> 00:09:32,766
实际上

570
00:09:32,766 --> 00:09:35,766
我们可以从无线网络中为它提供能量

571
00:09:36,066 --> 00:09:37,566
这是一个虚拟电网

572
00:09:37,566 --> 00:09:39,766
具有几乎无限的功率容量

573
00:09:39,766 --> 00:09:43,900
能够与高级电容交换电量

574
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:47,433
一旦能量与无线电网重新平衡

575
00:09:47,433 --> 00:09:49,100
搅拌机便可以使用了

576
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,566
但这并没有真正解决问题

577
00:09:51,566 --> 00:09:54,500

我们只是把问题转移到了聚变反应堆上


578
00:09:54,666 --> 00:09:57,400
而它们生产等离子的速度跟不上了

579
00:09:57,800 --> 00:10:00,400
这不是唯一的核聚变问题

580
00:10:00,566 --> 00:10:04,166
我们也遇到了亚稳态鿫的生产问题

581
00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:07,400
它们由小MK4反应堆制作的

582
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,266
为解决这些问题

583
00:10:09,266 --> 00:10:11,833
我们应该做一个压缩聚变MK4

584
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,400
它拥有更高的并行

585
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,233
不同于前者

586
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:17,966
它能执行无损超频

587
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:23,700
在t1配方上，压聚4将比压聚3快16倍

588
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:24,966
要制作它

589
00:10:24,966 --> 00:10:28,033
我们只缺铂金和一种塑料

590
00:10:28,066 --> 00:10:30,500
这些问题的常规解法

591
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,766
是升级对应的缓存

592
00:10:32,766 --> 00:10:35,266
或者是找到产线中的瓶颈

593
00:10:35,266 --> 00:10:36,466
并加快速度

594
00:10:36,766 --> 00:10:37,166
然而

595
00:10:37,166 --> 00:10:40,033
这是一项已变得难以管理的任务

596
00:10:40,033 --> 00:10:41,966
并且开始导致卡顿

597
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:44,366
我们现在有一个更好的解决方案

598
00:10:44,366 --> 00:10:47,166
来处理那些前期的长产线

599
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:48,900
量子操纵者

600
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:51,666
它可以一步完成整条铂处理

601
00:10:51,666 --> 00:10:54,766
可以轻松超频和并行

602
00:10:54,833 --> 00:10:58,633
我们再也不用处理这些流体了

603
00:10:58,633 --> 00:10:59,633
对于塑料

604
00:10:59,633 --> 00:11:02,800
一次性不会只制作聚苯并咪唑

605
00:11:02,966 --> 00:11:06,900
它也会同时做所有其他更简单的聚合物

606
00:11:06,966 --> 00:11:08,966
这就是我们的新机器

607
00:11:08,966 --> 00:11:11,833
一步就能产出大量塑料

608
00:11:11,966 --> 00:11:14,100
当我们的塑料在囤积

609
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:17,400
我们可以制造第二台加工铂金的机器

610
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:19,866
由于这台机器速度非常快

611
00:11:19,866 --> 00:11:22,566
即使催化剂很少、耗能很低

612
00:11:22,566 --> 00:11:24,766
我们可以清理旧产线了

613
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:25,966
同时

614
00:11:25,966 --> 00:11:30,800
我们已经收集到新聚变反应堆所需的所有材料

615
00:11:30,966 --> 00:11:34,833
在建造更多机器来处理所有东西之后

616
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:37,200
我们完成了新的反应堆

617
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,000
这个反应堆可太快了

618
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,866
瓶颈现在已经是搅拌机了

619
00:11:42,066 --> 00:11:43,866
但我们可以快速解决这个问题

620
00:11:43,866 --> 00:11:46,066
通过增加其最大并行

621
00:11:46,066 --> 00:11:48,200
让其使用我们所有的电力

622
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:50,866
当搅拌机等待剩余能量

623
00:11:50,866 --> 00:11:53,033
被发送进无线网络时

624
00:11:53,033 --> 00:11:55,033
我们可以制造更多的机器

625
00:11:55,033 --> 00:11:58,033
加快戴森球的制作速度

626
00:11:58,366 --> 00:12:00,833
通过使用植物魔法中的洛基戒指

627
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:04,066
我们甚至可以并行制造机器

628
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:06,666
有了这些新机器

629
00:12:06,666 --> 00:12:10,266
我们很快就完成了新能源的所有部分

630
00:12:10,266 --> 00:12:11,633
戴森球

631
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,200

这个结构的问题是


632
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,700
我们用来包裹恒星的模块

633
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,966
最终会滑行，从而破裂

634
00:12:18,066 --> 00:12:20,566
所以我们必须不断地发射新模块

635
00:12:20,566 --> 00:12:24,666
和更多算力来更好地计算模块轨迹

636
00:12:24,666 --> 00:12:27,000
降低所需的替代品

637
00:12:27,233 --> 00:12:30,266
要把所有的能量转移回基地

638
00:12:30,266 --> 00:12:33,000
我们可以再制造一个真·终极电池

639
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:36,166
但我觉得虫洞发生器听起来更酷

640
00:12:36,433 --> 00:12:38,400
这样我们就有了足够的能量

641
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:41,000
进一步加快海珀珍的生产

642
00:12:41,266 --> 00:12:44,166
有了40000A的UHV电

643
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:48,066
产量从每秒半个锭上升至超过两个锭

644
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:51,233
为了进一步提高DTPF产能

645
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:54,766

我们用海珀珍来增加DTPF的数量


646
00:12:55,033 --> 00:12:58,566
即使在该功率下运行4个DTPF

647
00:12:58,566 --> 00:13:02,500
每秒时空产量也不到一个锭

648
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:05,700
但是如果我们能得到永恒线圈

649
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:11,400
我们可以用不到一半的原料做四倍的量

650
00:13:11,566 --> 00:13:14,033
主要问题是永恒线圈

651
00:13:14,033 --> 00:13:16,433
除了需要相当多的时空

652
00:13:16,433 --> 00:13:17,966
和UIV电路

653
00:13:17,966 --> 00:13:20,766
也需要一个永恒奇点

654
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:22,600
做这些东西很贵

655
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:24,500
而且还需要一些东西

656
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:27,700
比如我们还没有真正自动化的灵魂沙

657
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:31,466
只用几块灵魂沙做一个奇点

658
00:13:31,466 --> 00:13:32,466
是完全可以接受的

659
00:13:32,466 --> 00:13:34,800
现在我们必须找到更好的方法

660
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:38,666
我认为最好的方法是完全不使用灵魂沙

661
00:13:38,666 --> 00:13:43,200
我们可以通过压缩一点时空得到奇点

662
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:43,700
然而

663
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:46,300
这需要一个稳定的黑洞

664
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:49,166
这又是一条不归路

665
00:13:49,366 --> 00:13:51,466
我认为这是一个很好的时机……

666
00:13:51,466 --> 00:13:52,600
来开始研究它

667
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:55,666
因为这是当前电压的最后一个主要任务

668
00:13:55,866 --> 00:13:59,033
所以在处理了数百万个铁粉后

669
00:13:59,033 --> 00:14:00,600
我们建立了一个结构

670
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,600
强大到足以支撑和容纳黑洞

671
00:14:03,766 --> 00:14:06,833
这台机器有一些特殊要求

672
00:14:06,966 --> 00:14:07,266
第一

673
00:14:07,266 --> 00:14:10,200
我们需要黑洞种子来打开黑洞

674
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,033
这样我们就可以压缩东西了

675
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:15,066
一旦黑洞变得不稳定

676
00:14:15,066 --> 00:14:16,800
我们用黑洞坍缩器来关闭它

677
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:19,766
所以一旦一切准备就绪

678
00:14:19,766 --> 00:14:22,166
我们可以把黑洞种子扔进机器里

679
00:14:22,166 --> 00:14:23,833
欣赏我们所创造的东西

680
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:27,566
我们用它来制造永恒奇点

681
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:31,400
然而我们的黑洞将慢慢衰变

682
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:33,966

逐渐无法继续生产


683
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,500
在那种状态下

684
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:38,433
它会吞噬我们的材料

685
00:14:38,466 --> 00:14:41,466
所以我们让它坍缩来重置机器

686
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:45,000
现在是时候完全自动化这个过程了

687
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:47,200
在做了一点数学运算之后

688
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,400
我们发现

689
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:51,200
通过添加一些额外的稳定剂

690
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:56,500
我们可以用一个黑洞制造出2800个奇点

691
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:59,600
所以我们快速编写一个样板

692
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:02,300
包含了所有需要的东西

693
00:15:02,666 --> 00:15:04,000
材料将被拆分

694
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:07,600
这样一组计时器就能妥善管理黑洞

695
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:12,266
第一个是让黑洞接近其寿命的终点

696
00:15:12,466 --> 00:15:13,900
在此阶段

697
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:18,233
黑洞可以让我们一次产生88个奇点

698
00:15:18,566 --> 00:15:19,200
然后

699
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,000
就在临界点之前

700
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,233
计时器将触发第二个计时器

701
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:28,400
它将通过在黑洞中插入熔融时空来阻止黑洞的衰变

702
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:31,400
材料成本指数增长

703
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:31,633
所以

704
00:15:31,633 --> 00:15:35,033
我们不想让这个过程持续太久

705
00:15:35,033 --> 00:15:36,633
而在这个阶段

706
00:15:36,633 --> 00:15:41,866
我们的黑洞将一次压缩350个物品

707
00:15:42,666 --> 00:15:46,033
一旦稳定器成本过高

708
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:47,600
我们就把黑洞坍塌

709
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:50,633
现在我们有足够的奇点了

710
00:15:50,633 --> 00:15:54,200
我们可以开始研究最后一级线圈了

711
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:57,500
这要求我们建造一套新的固化器

712
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,966
来获得所有的锭和螺丝

713
00:16:00,266 --> 00:16:03,600
然后我们的线缆厂准备好了电缆

714
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:08,100
最后是我们所有的14条通用装配线

715
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:10,633
我们慢慢制作新的线圈

716
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:15,666
当我们制作DTPF升级所需的7000个线圈时

717
00:16:15,666 --> 00:16:20,166
我们也可以利用奇点来升级矿处

718
00:16:20,433 --> 00:16:23,300
问题是我们不能让矿处运转

719
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:26,266
因为它会很快塞满存储元件

720
00:16:26,466 --> 00:16:29,200
但现在我们可以负担得起更好的存储

721
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:35,433
我们将用它来储存产线中出产的近乎无穷的物品

722
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:36,433
同时

723
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:38,766
修好AFK计时器后

724
00:16:38,766 --> 00:16:42,700
我们储备了足够的线圈来升级DTPF

725
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:43,500
用那些

726
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:45,866
我们现在可以制造更便宜的时空

727
00:16:45,866 --> 00:16:47,200
廉价的海珀珍

728
00:16:47,266 --> 00:16:49,966
从单一催化剂中取出一堆无尽

729
00:16:49,966 --> 00:16:52,166
以及许多其他后期游戏配方

730
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:53,200
有了这个

731
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:55,900
